cdx6500T1CfgPortType.description: This is a digital port having interface type T1. t1 : This is a T1 port.

cdx6500T1CfgFormat.description: This parameter is used to select the format of the T1 interface. channelize : DS0 definition fixed, predefined by the telco or the user. isdn : DS0 definition defined by the ISDN D channel. nc : Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500T1CfgLineFramingType.name: cdx6500T1CfgLineFramingType
cdx6500T1CfgLineFramingType.description: Indicates the type of framing used by the DS1 circuit. esf : Extended SuperFrame. sf : SuperFrame. nc : Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500T1CfgLineCoding.name: cdx6500T1CfgLineCoding
cdx6500T1CfgLineCoding.description: Selects the type of suppression used on the T1 link. b8zs :Bipolar 8 Zero Substitution. b7zs :Bipolar 7 zero Substitution. ami :Alternate Mark Inversion. nc : Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500T1CfgTransmitClock.name: cdx6500T1CfgTransmitClock
cdx6500T1CfgTransmitClock.description: Selects the source of the transmit clock. int : Internal Oscillator. rec : Received Timing. node : Node Timing (timing off another interface). nc : Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500T1CfgLineBuildOut.name: cdx6500T1CfgLineBuildOut
cdx6500T1CfgLineBuildOut.description: Select the Line Build Out to match the physical interface. For DSX interfaces, this value is based on cable length as explained below :- lbo0 : 0 ft to 133 ft lbo1 :134 ft to 266 ft lbo2 :267 ft to 399 ft lbo3 :400 ft to 533 ft lbo4 :534 ft to 655 ft For DS1 interfaces, this value is based on the signal level as explained below :- lbo0 : 0 db lbo1 : -7.5 db lbo2 : -15 db lbo3 : -22.5db lbo4 : not valid for DS1 interfaces. nc : Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500T1CfgFacilityDataLink.name: cdx6500T1CfgFacilityDataLink
cdx6500T1CfgFacilityDataLink.description: This describes the use of the facilities data link, and may have the following capabilities: none : indicates that the device does not use the FDL. ansi : refers to the FDL exchange recommended by ANSI (Ansi-T1-403). att : refers to ESF FDL exchanges (Att-54016). nc : Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500T1CfgThresholdValueLES.name: cdx6500T1CfgThresholdValueLES
cdx6500T1CfgThresholdValueLES.description: Threshold value of Line Errored Seconds (LESs) to report alarms on CTP when exceeded.

cdx6500T1CfgSwitchType.name: cdx6500T1CfgSwitchType
cdx6500T1CfgSwitchType.description: The ISDN switch type. This specifies the type of equipment to which this span is connected. The possible choices are: att4ess : AT&T 4ESS Switch att5ess : AT&T 5ESS Switch ntDms100 : Northern Telecom DMS-100 Switch ntDms250 : Northern Telecom DMS-250 Switch md110Us : Ericsson MD-110 (North America) md110 : Ericsson MD-110 (International) siemens : Siemens EWSD Switch (U.S.) ntt : Nippon Telephone and Telegraph switch (Japan) unknown : Unknown Switch Type nc : Skipped during configuration

cdx6500T1CfgVariant.name: cdx6500T1CfgVariant
cdx6500T1CfgVariant.description: Select the ISDN Switch variant. This parameter depends upon the switch type configured. The possible choices are: att : AT&T Custom nt : Northern Telecom isdn2 : Bellcore National ISDN-2 jate : JATE-compatible (Japan) net5 : NET-5 standard (Europe) oneTr6 : 1TR6 standard for PRI (Germany) vn3 : VN3 standard (France) ccitt : General CCITT Q.931 conformance ts014 : AUSTEL TS014 standard (Australia) nc : Skipped during configuration

cdx6500T1CfgUserNetworkSide.name: cdx6500T1CfgUserNetworkSide
cdx6500T1CfgUserNetworkSide.description: This parameter specifies whether the T1/E1 port is emulating the network or user side of the ISDN network. user : The T1 or E1 port is emulating the user, ex. the T1 or E1 port is to be connected to an ISDN network. network : The T1 or E1 port is emulating the network, ex. the T1 or E1 port is to be connected to an ISDN PBX. nc : Skipped during configuration.
